  "post_stream": {
    "posts": [
      {
        "id": 2408537,
        "name": "Dennis Atick",
        "username": "Dennis_Atick",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/dennis_atick/{size}/429_2.png",
        "created_at": "2018-05-03T15:46:30.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Had a nice evening with good guys and great food and a eclectic mix of really terrific wine at Staplehouse in Atlanta last night. I tried to take some notes, which I did for a bit, but then lost track. There was also a '85 Pousse d\u2019Or Bousse d\u2019Or and '83 St Amour that are obvious omissions from my list. A Clos Rougeard, too. Tough night when there\u2019s so much good wine you lose track of Rougeard  <img src=\"/uploads/db3686/original/2X/0/0ff9bfcdb0964982cd3240b6159868fbdf215b1a.gif\" width=\"24\" height=\"18\" alt=\"[cheers.gif]\" title=\"cheers\" class=\"animated\">  Oh, and a '29 Cognac that was ridic.<br>\nAll the wines showed really well. Great stuff. Thanks guys, and fill in my gaps here if you will.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/note.asp?iWine=2359185&amp;iNote=7007899\"><strong>2014 J\u00e9r\u00f4me Pr\u00e9vost Champagne La Closerie Extra Brut Les Beguines</strong></a> <em>- France, Champagne (5/3/2018)</em><br>\nReally terrific again. Oxidative and rich on the palate. Terrific sweet/salty thing going on. Rich on the palate, but light on its feet. Refreshing melon/honey notes. After an hour, it picked up bready/buttery flavors. Love this stuff.</li>\n<li>\n<a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/note.asp?iWine=19863&amp;iNote=7008002\"><strong>1999 Ch\u00e2teau Haut-Brion Blanc</strong></a> <em>- France, Bordeaux, Graves, Pessac-L\u00e9ognan (5/3/2018)</em><br>\nAmazing wine. Decanted about 30 minutes. So deep and penetrating. Nutty and buttery and the most amazing waxy texture on the palate. Still carries a lively acidity. Came back to a glass about an hour later and a kaleidescope of flavors and tones were racing around and there was more of a minerality present. The finish was crazy long and just lingered all over the palate. On and on and on\u2026really terrific wine. [/i]</li>\n<li>\n<a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/note.asp?iWine=283089&amp;iNote=7007897\"><strong>2005 Bonneau du Martray Corton-Charlemagne</strong></a> <em>- France, Burgundy, C\u00f4te de Beaune, Corton-Charlemagne Grand Cru (5/3/2018)</em><br>\nA sound bottle of BdM! It does happen! Pronounced Buttered popcorn nose I get from CC at times. Green apple and richness on the palate. Really youthful still, but starting to drink. Prob needs a decant, we had too many bottles flowing. Coats the palate with great energy and sails on. Good wine.</li>\n<li>\n<a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/note.asp?iWine=1220034&amp;iNote=7008007\"><strong>1995 Kalin Cellars Chardonnay</strong></a> <em>- USA, California, Sonoma County, Sonoma Coast (5/3/2018)</em><br>\nStill full of juicy life. Buttery, rich and full textured, forward fruit, more obviously Cali than the Burg before. There is nice cut from the acid which balances the depth. Honestly, I wouldn\u2019t hurry to drink these if I owned. Really a great showing.</li>\n<li>\n<a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/note.asp?iWine=2984790&amp;iNote=7008025\"><strong>1978 Jacques Parent Corton</strong></a> <em>- France, Burgundy, C\u00f4te de Beaune, Corton Grand Cru (5/3/2018)</em><br>\nEverything I want in aged Burgundy nose. Dank, earthy, sweet spice. Still lively on the palate, soft red fruit lingers with some tea and asian spice. Very pretty wine. Begins to fade a bit with time. But the best and most ready Corton I\u2019ve had in some time. [/i]</li>\n<li>\n<a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/note.asp?iWine=429119&amp;iNote=7008009\"><strong>1985 Joseph Drouhin Savigny-l\u00e8s-Beaune</strong></a> <em>- France, Burgundy, C\u00f4te de Beaune, Savigny-l\u00e8s-Beaune (5/3/2018)</em><br>\nAll I\u2019m going to say is that this wine confirms that I drink village wines too young and just don\u2019t pay them enough attention. Excellent showing. So good. __</li>\n</ul>\n<p><em>Posted from <a href=\"https://www.cellartracker.com/\">CellarTracker</a><br>\nA couple of pics, including the crazy crab dish wrapped in  gelee like a clear dumpling.</em><br>\n<img src=\"/uploads/db3686/original/3X/2/d/2d655a94b089361d3a749ce44b46bc057c55a456.jpeg\" alt=\"20180502_191816.jpg\" data-base62-sha1=\"6tADpPA6hA5OoJLnbTaCPVhDlmS\" width=\"270\" height=\"480\"><br>\n<img src=\"/uploads/db3686/original/3X/e/0/e00b72c32bf33bf1266bd6cd67a51359279459ae.jpeg\" alt=\"20180502_202012.jpg\" data-base62-sha1=\"vXZtPQAN04GnBQNNhGo26YvR5X8\" width=\"270\" height=\"480\"><br>\n<img src=\"/uploads/db3686/original/3X/b/e/be178038410a1941b90a0c6c50e9aed2cd591875.jpeg\" alt=\"IMG_20180502_201534_120.jpg\" data-base62-sha1=\"r7D4k5vCjOmd0qRT6dHvu7Mbw0J\" width=\"480\" height=\"480\"><br>\n<img src=\"/uploads/db3686/original/3X/c/5/c58b7cac57283313be6cf0e143a15aff360cccde.jpeg\" alt=\"20180502_184241.jpg\" data-base62-sha1=\"sbyUuGk9gaEijGPTBNEp5DxVXnU\" width=\"270\" height=\"480\"><br>\n<img src=\"/uploads/db3686/original/3X/2/9/29e2c3bcda42c8099e0779f1580af7bd7f5c52b4.jpeg\" alt=\"20180502_182026.jpg\" data-base62-sha1=\"5YxpRJqf3aai20Jm76z1zMIJzve\" width=\"640\" height=\"360\"></p>",
